quran[11]{c,v,t}:
  27,83,"Some day We shall summon a troop from every nation which has rejected Our signs, and they will be paraded forth"
  27,84,"until, when they come [before God], He will say: \"Did you reject My signs and not grasp any knowledge concerning them? What have you been doing"
  27,85,"The Sentence will prevail against them because of the wrong they have committed. They will not utter [a word]"
  27,86,"Have they not considered how We have made night so they may rest in it, and daylight so they can see? In that are signs for folk who believe"
  27,87,"Someday the Trumpet will be blown and startle whoever is in Heaven and whoever is on Earth, except for anyone God may wish. Everyone will come to Him abjectly"
  27,88,"You will see the mountains, which you reckoned were solid, slip away just as clouds slip away, through the handiwork of God Who consummates everything. He is Informed about whatever you are doing"
  27,89,Anyone who comes with a fine deed will have something better than it and they will be safe from that day´s terror
  27,90,"while anyone who comes with an evil deed will be flung face down into the Fire: \"Aren´t you rewarded with just what you´ve been doing"
  27,91,I have only been ordered to serve the Lord of this region which He has hallowed. He possesses everything. I have been ordered to be a Muslim
  27,92,"and to recite the Quran. Anyone who is guided, will be guided only for his own sake, while tell anyone who strays away: ´I am merely a warner"
  27,93,"SAY: \"Praise be to God! He will show you His signs so you may recognize them. Your Lord is not overlooking anything you do"